{
  "texts": [
    "Further, group convolutions allow these views to explicitly interact in a way that does not break symmetries.",
    "Here lies the key difference between the two approaches: frame averaging and group convolutions rigorously enforce the symmetries in G, whereas data augmentation only provides implicit hints to the model about satisfying them.",
    "As a consequence of the exhaustive generation, Eqs.",
    "(6) and (8) are only feasible for small groups like D 2.",
    "For larger groups, approaches like Steerable CNNs 27 may be employed."
  ]
}